The paper deals with testing of component oriented systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on labeled transition systems with inputs and outputs (LTSs), which is a topic that falls under the category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). The paper also mentions finite state machines (FSMs), which is a related topic in formal languages and automata theory. The algorithm proposed in the paper is a generalization of an algorithm for computing adaptive distinguishing sequences for FSMs, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper deals with the practical implementation of the algorithm on an industrial benchmark, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the category of emerging technologies (cs.ET).
